      * ----------------------------------------------------------------
      * Project: {project_name}
      * Member : {member_name}
      * Desc   : {description}
      * Author : {author_name}
      * Date   : {creation_date}
      * ----------------------------------------------------------------

       IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
       PROGRAM-ID. {program_name}.
       AUTHOR. {author_name}.
       DATE-WRITTEN. {creation_date}.
       DATE-COMPILED.

      *----------------------------------------------------------------
      * ENVIRONMENT DIVISION
      *----------------------------------------------------------------
       ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.

       CONFIGURATION SECTION.
       SOURCE-COMPUTER. IBM-ISERIES.
       OBJECT-COMPUTER. IBM-ISERIES.

       INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.
       FILE-CONTROL.
      *    SELECT INPUT-FILE
      *        ASSIGN TO DATABASE-{input_file}
      *        ORGANIZATION IS INDEXED
      *        ACCESS MODE IS DYNAMIC
      *        RECORD KEY IS INPUT-KEY
      *        FILE STATUS IS INPUT-FILE-STATUS.
      *
      *    SELECT OUTPUT-FILE
      *        ASSIGN TO DATABASE-{output_file}
      *        ORGANIZATION IS SEQUENTIAL
      *        FILE STATUS IS OUTPUT-FILE-STATUS.

      *----------------------------------------------------------------
      * DATA DIVISION
      *----------------------------------------------------------------
       DATA DIVISION.

       FILE SECTION.
      *FD  INPUT-FILE
      *    LABEL RECORDS ARE STANDARD.
      *01  INPUT-RECORD.
      *    05  INPUT-KEY           PIC X(10).
      *    05  INPUT-DATA          PIC X(100).
      *
      *FD  OUTPUT-FILE
      *    LABEL RECORDS ARE STANDARD.
      *01  OUTPUT-RECORD.
      *    05  OUTPUT-DATA         PIC X(132).

       WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.

      *----------------------------------------------------------------
      * Program Constants
      *----------------------------------------------------------------
       01  PROGRAM-CONSTANTS.
           05  PROGRAM-NAME        PIC X(10) VALUE '{program_name}'.
           05  PROGRAM-VERSION     PIC X(10) VALUE '1.0.0'.
           05  SUCCESS-CODE        PIC 9(02) VALUE 00.
           05  ERROR-CODE          PIC 9(02) VALUE 99.

      *----------------------------------------------------------------
      * File Status Variables
      *----------------------------------------------------------------
       01  FILE-STATUS-FIELDS.
           05  INPUT-FILE-STATUS   PIC XX.
               88  INPUT-FILE-OK   VALUE '00'.
               88  INPUT-FILE-EOF  VALUE '10'.
           05  OUTPUT-FILE-STATUS  PIC XX.
               88  OUTPUT-FILE-OK  VALUE '00'.

      *----------------------------------------------------------------
      * Work Variables
      *----------------------------------------------------------------
       01  WORK-FIELDS.
           05  WS-RETURN-CODE      PIC 9(02) VALUE ZERO.
           05  WS-RECORD-COUNT     PIC 9(05) VALUE ZERO.
           05  WS-ERROR-COUNT      PIC 9(05) VALUE ZERO.
           05  WS-CURRENT-DATE     PIC 9(08).
           05  WS-CURRENT-TIME     PIC 9(06).
           05  WS-MESSAGE          PIC X(100).

      *----------------------------------------------------------------
      * Switches and Indicators
      *----------------------------------------------------------------
       01  PROGRAM-SWITCHES.
           05  END-OF-FILE-SW      PIC X VALUE 'N'.
               88  END-OF-FILE     VALUE 'Y'.
               88  NOT-END-OF-FILE VALUE 'N'.
           05  ERROR-FOUND-SW      PIC X VALUE 'N'.
               88  ERROR-FOUND     VALUE 'Y'.
               88  NO-ERROR-FOUND  VALUE 'N'.
           05  FIRST-TIME-SW       PIC X VALUE 'Y'.
               88  FIRST-TIME      VALUE 'Y'.
               88  NOT-FIRST-TIME  VALUE 'N'.

      *----------------------------------------------------------------
      * Data Structures
      *----------------------------------------------------------------
       01  CUSTOMER-RECORD.
           05  CUST-ID             PIC 9(10).
           05  CUST-NAME           PIC X(50).
           05  CUST-ADDRESS        PIC X(100).
           05  CUST-STATUS         PIC X.
               88  CUST-ACTIVE     VALUE 'A'.
               88  CUST-INACTIVE   VALUE 'I'.
           05  CUST-BALANCE        PIC S9(13)V99 COMP-3.

      *----------------------------------------------------------------
      * Error Information
      *----------------------------------------------------------------
       01  ERROR-INFO.
           05  ERROR-PARAGRAPH     PIC X(30).
           05  ERROR-MESSAGE       PIC X(100).
           05  ERROR-SQLCODE       PIC S9(09) COMP-5.

      *----------------------------------------------------------------
      * PROCEDURE DIVISION
      *----------------------------------------------------------------
       PROCEDURE DIVISION.

      *----------------------------------------------------------------
      * Main Control Paragraph
      *----------------------------------------------------------------
       0000-MAIN-CONTROL.
           PERFORM 1000-INITIALIZATION
           IF NO-ERROR-FOUND
               PERFORM 2000-PROCESS-RECORDS
                   UNTIL END-OF-FILE OR ERROR-FOUND
               PERFORM 3000-TERMINATION
           END-IF
           STOP RUN.

      *----------------------------------------------------------------
      * Initialization
      *----------------------------------------------------------------
       1000-INITIALIZATION.
           DISPLAY 'Starting ' PROGRAM-NAME
           ACCEPT WS-CURRENT-DATE FROM DATE YYYYMMDD
           ACCEPT WS-CURRENT-TIME FROM TIME

           MOVE ZERO TO WS-RECORD-COUNT
           MOVE ZERO TO WS-ERROR-COUNT
           SET NOT-END-OF-FILE TO TRUE
           SET NO-ERROR-FOUND TO TRUE
           SET FIRST-TIME TO TRUE

      *    OPEN INPUT INPUT-FILE
      *    IF NOT INPUT-FILE-OK
      *        MOVE 'Error opening input file' TO WS-MESSAGE
      *        PERFORM 9000-ERROR-ROUTINE
      *    END-IF
      *
      *    OPEN OUTPUT OUTPUT-FILE
      *    IF NOT OUTPUT-FILE-OK
      *        MOVE 'Error opening output file' TO WS-MESSAGE
      *        PERFORM 9000-ERROR-ROUTINE
      *    END-IF

           DISPLAY 'Initialization complete'.

      *----------------------------------------------------------------
      * Process Records
      *----------------------------------------------------------------
       2000-PROCESS-RECORDS.
      *    PERFORM 2100-READ-INPUT-FILE
      *    IF NOT END-OF-FILE AND NO-ERROR-FOUND
      *        PERFORM 2200-PROCESS-RECORD
      *        IF NO-ERROR-FOUND
      *            PERFORM 2300-WRITE-OUTPUT-FILE
      *        END-IF
      *    END-IF
           .

      *----------------------------------------------------------------
      * Read Input File
      *----------------------------------------------------------------
       2100-READ-INPUT-FILE.
      *    READ INPUT-FILE
      *        AT END
      *            SET END-OF-FILE TO TRUE
      *        NOT AT END
      *            ADD 1 TO WS-RECORD-COUNT
      *    END-READ
      *
      *    IF NOT INPUT-FILE-OK AND NOT INPUT-FILE-EOF
      *        MOVE 'Error reading input file' TO WS-MESSAGE
      *        PERFORM 9000-ERROR-ROUTINE
      *    END-IF
           .

      *----------------------------------------------------------------
      * Process Record
      *----------------------------------------------------------------
       2200-PROCESS-RECORD.
      *    TODO: Add your record processing logic here
      *
      *    Example: Validate customer status
      *    IF NOT CUST-ACTIVE AND NOT CUST-INACTIVE
      *        MOVE 'Invalid customer status' TO WS-MESSAGE
      *        PERFORM 9000-ERROR-ROUTINE
      *    END-IF
           .

      *----------------------------------------------------------------
      * Write Output File
      *----------------------------------------------------------------
       2300-WRITE-OUTPUT-FILE.
      *    WRITE OUTPUT-RECORD
      *    IF NOT OUTPUT-FILE-OK
      *        MOVE 'Error writing output file' TO WS-MESSAGE
      *        PERFORM 9000-ERROR-ROUTINE
      *    END-IF
           .

      *----------------------------------------------------------------
      * Termination
      *----------------------------------------------------------------
       3000-TERMINATION.
      *    CLOSE INPUT-FILE
      *    CLOSE OUTPUT-FILE

           DISPLAY 'Records processed: ' WS-RECORD-COUNT
           DISPLAY 'Errors encountered: ' WS-ERROR-COUNT

           IF ERROR-FOUND
               MOVE ERROR-CODE TO WS-RETURN-CODE
               DISPLAY 'Program ended with errors'
           ELSE
               MOVE SUCCESS-CODE TO WS-RETURN-CODE
               DISPLAY 'Program completed successfully'
           END-IF

           DISPLAY 'Ending ' PROGRAM-NAME.

      *----------------------------------------------------------------
      * Error Routine
      *----------------------------------------------------------------
       9000-ERROR-ROUTINE.
           ADD 1 TO WS-ERROR-COUNT
           SET ERROR-FOUND TO TRUE
           DISPLAY 'ERROR: ' WS-MESSAGE
           DISPLAY 'Error count: ' WS-ERROR-COUNT.

      *----------------------------------------------------------------
      * End of Program
      *----------------------------------------------------------------
